             </layout>
            </widget>
           </item>
           <item>
            <widget class="QGroupBox" name="groupBox_stem_separation">
             <property name="toolTip">
              <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700;&quot;&gt;What is audio stem separation?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Traditionally, Singstar/Ultrastar uses the music video of a song as the audio track. Real karaoke without the original singer's voice was not possible. This is mostly due to availability: a song having an official vocals-less version is rare. The timing would have to be the exact same to match up with the lyrics/music video.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;However, AI makes it possible to split an audio file into a vocals and an instrumental track. From V1.1.0 on, the Ultrastar format standardizes tags for a game to find these tracks. Currently, at least USDX and Ultrastar Play/Melody Mania support this. So all we need to do is actually run the AI separation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Running AI reliably on a wide array of user machines is tricky. Some users may benefit greatly from using CUDA or other GPU acceleration. Others may prefer a cloud upload to allow separation at all. We have chosen a modular approach that allows for all of these needs to be met.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700;&quot;&gt;How to use in USDB Syncer?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. You need a separation provider. We have developed a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/bohning/usdb_syncer_separation&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline; color:#3586ff;&quot;&gt;reference provider&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that utilizes &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/adefossez/demucs&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; text-decoration: underline; color:#3586ff;&quot;&gt;demucs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Follow the steps of your provider to download/build the executable you need and place the executable in a folder of your choosing.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Enable the stem separation checkbox here in the Settings and select the executable you just downloaded/built via the &lt;img src=&quot;:/icons/arrow-split.png&quot;/&gt; button.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. Select the model you wish to use. Consult the documentation of your provider for which model yields best results.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. Select the number of simultaneous separations. Local separation is incredibly taxing, so we recommend starting with a low value.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
             </property>
             <property name="title">
              <string>Separate audio stems (beta)</string>
             </property>
             <property name="alignment">
              <set>Qt::AlignmentFlag::AlignLeading|Qt::AlignmentFlag::AlignLeft|Qt::AlignmentFlag::AlignTop</set>
             </property>
             <property name="checkable">
              <bool>true</bool>
             </property>
             <property name="checked">
              <bool>false</bool>
             </property>
             <layout class="QGridLayout" name="gridLayout_audio_stems" columnstretch="0,0,1,0,0">
              <item row="2" column="0">
               <widget class="QLabel" name="label_separation_threads">
